Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more details. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The Wits Students Representative Council says it will meet with management this weekend. This follows escalated protests at the Braamfontein campus on Friday. Wits University students intensify protest Protesting students want to end financial exclusions, more student accommodation, and higher residence allowances.  The Wits Students Representative Council says it will be meeting with management this weekend.  Shortly after a meeting with management, SRC president Aphiwe Mnyamana spoke to reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones. At the same time, Wits University says it can't address protesting students' demands as they are based on untrue claims.  Talks between Wits management and student representatives have deadlocked. The university says it will not be suspending its academic programme amid the student protests. Wits spokesperson, Shirona Patel speaks to #eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403